<HEADLINE> O'Donnell's Home Deal Falls Through  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   VALLEY COTTAGE. N.Y. (AP) -- It looks like there won't be a
Rockland County encore for Rosie O'Donnell.
</P>
<P>
   The comedian's deal for a $1.95 million home in Valley Cottage
has fallen through, real estate brokers said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   O'Donnell lived in nearby Nyack until December, when she moved
to Greenwich, Conn. She caused an uproar there when a bodyguard
hired to protect her oldest son applied for a concealed-weapon
permit.
</P>
<P>
   The National Rifle Association officials accused O'Donnell, a
gun control advocate, of hypocrisy.
</P>
<P>
   Broker Russ Woolley said he was told O'Donnell found another
home in the metropolitan area but he did not know where.
</P>
</TEXT>
