<HEADLINE> Russian Nationalist Slain in Belarus  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINSK, Belarus (AP) -- The leader of an ultranationalist Russian
group was stabbed to death and the director of a glass factory was
shot and killed, police said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The body of Gleb Samoilov, leader of the Russian National Unity
organization, was found Saturday in a corridor of his apartment
house, Sergei Kolbasov, chief of the city's homicide department,
told the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
   A preliminary investigation indicated that Samoilov left his
apartment early Saturday after receiving a telephone call. His body
was found a short while later by neighbors, Kolbasov said.
</P>
