<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fake lawyer sentenced to one year in jail  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - A man who admitted practicing as an
immigration lawyer for more than a decade without a license was
sentenced to a year in jail and must pay $50,000 in restitution.
</P>
<P>
   Robert Callan, 61, said Friday he never meant to hurt anyone.
</P>
<P>
   ''The majority of people that came into the office were
helped,'' said the Trenton resident, who ran The Immigration Law
Center in Ewing for more than 10 years. ''These people need help,
and there was little help available.''
</P>
<P>
   Mercer County Assistant Prosecutor Lawrence McGivney said Callan
preyed on people who dreamed of coming to America. He said many
were deported because Callan didn't handle their cases properly.
</P>
<P>
   McGivney called Callan ''a con man of the highest order.''
</P>
<P>
   McGivney said the scheme was discovered when one victim, a
Russian businessman, called the Bar Association to check Callan's
credentials.
</P>
<P>
   In April, Callan pleaded guilty to practicing law without a
license, theft by deception and attempted theft by deception.
</P>
<P>
   Superior Court Judge Paul Innes on Friday said Callan ''preyed
on these people who were extremely vulnerable. Mr. Callan's actions
resulted in the forfeiture of their dreams.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
