<HEADLINE> Train tangled in wires stalls service to New York  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MILFORD, Conn. (AP) - Passengers were stranded aboard a
Metro-North Railroad train for about two hours Saturday after the
train became tangled in wires, stalling service to New York for
hours.
</P>
<P>
   The train, on its way to New York, got tangled in downed wires
in Milford about 8 a.m., stalling service on all four tracks, said
Metro-North spokeswoman Marjorie Anders. The downed wires affected
service originating from Bridgeport to New Haven.
</P>
<P>
   Service on one track was restored about 10 a.m. after the
passengers were rescued.
</P>
<P>
   One track was able to accommodate the lighter weekend schedule
and all four tracks were expected to be running Monday morning,
Anders said.
</P>
<P>
   No injuries were reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
