<HEADLINE> With BC-NY--Telephone Talks  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Facts and figures about Verizon Communications:
<TEXT>
<P>
   -Formed in June by the merger of Bell Atlantic and GTE Corp.,
and based in New York.
</P>
<P>
   -The largest provider of local and wireless telephone service in
the United States.
</P>
<P>
   -Has about 95 million landline access lines in 31 states.
Provides local service in all 31 states.
</P>
<P>
   -Provides long distance in 38 states.
</P>
<P>
   -Serves about 25 million wireless customers in all 50 states via
a separate company in joint venture with Vodafone AirTouch.
</P>
<P>
   -More than $60 billion in revenue in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   -More than 260,000 employees in the United States and 40 other
nations. Its wireless division is its fastest growing, employing
about 32,000 workers.
</P>
</TEXT>
