<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-05 17:18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Witness in murder case is killed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) - He was expected to testify in an East Orange
murder case. Now Daniel Meronvil has himself become a murder
victim.
</P>
<P>
   He was shot to death last Sunday after leaving his job at Newark
Airport. His family members told The Star-Ledger of Newark for
Saturday's editions that he had testified before a grand jury that
indicted Damian Nelson, who is charged with the East Orange
slaying.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson is accused of shooting a close friend of Meronvil, Shily
Charles, 24, on Main Street Feb. 14. Meronvil's sister, Damaqu,
said her family feels her brother's killing was related to the
Charles slaying.
</P>
<P>
   ''He saw his friend shot in front of him and he testified about
what he saw,'' she said. ''We kind of feel this had something to do
with it.''
</P>
<P>
   Meronvil, 21, was one of two witnesses to the Charles killing
listed in a police report on the incident.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson, 19, was arrested at his East Orange home on Feb. 25 and
charged with murder and weapons offenses. He has been in jail since
then.
</P>
<P>
   A relative of Nelson said he doubted Nelson had anything to do
with Meronvil's death.
</P>
<P>
   ''Damian's locked up,'' said a man who answered the door at
Nelson's home and identified himself as a brother-in-law of the
suspect. He would not give his name. ''He does call home sometimes,
but all calls are monitored, so as for him having any connection,
that sounds far-fetched to me.''
</P>
<P>
   Meronvil was found in an empty lot near South 12th Street,
bleeding from a gunshot wound Sunday night after he left his job as
a janitor at Newark International Airport. He died several hours
later at University Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte Smith, a spokeswoman for the Essex County Prosecutor's
Office, would only confirm that Meronvil was shot to death. She
would not discuss details of the shooting, or whether Meronvil was
expected to testify against Nelson.
</P>
<P>
   The newspaper cited unidentified law enforcement officials who
said he was, in fact, scheduled to testify for the prosecution. It
was not clear when Nelson is due to stand trial.
</P>
<P>
   The officials would not say whether they have information
linking Meronvil's killing to Nelson.
</P>
<P>
   Family members told the newspaper that Meronvil died from
shotgun blasts to the leg and chest. They said they did not know if
he was on foot or driving when he was shot.
</P>
</TEXT>
