<HEADLINE> Moni Maker Wins Nat Ray Trot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Moni Maker became the first horse
in harness racing to surpass $5 million in career earnings, winning
the $500,000 Nat Ray trot Saturday in her final Meadowlands
Racetrack appearance.
</P>
<P>
   Moni Maker broke her own trotting record for mares, winning in
1:52.1, two fifths of a second better than her old mark.
</P>
<P>
   The win atoned for her loss in last week's Breeders Crown trot
in which the 7-year-old mare finished second to Magician.
</P>
<P>
   ''She's the greatest trotter that ever raced,'' said trainer
Jimmy Takter, who also said the mare will move to Canada for a few
races before retiring.
</P>
<P>
   Longtime driver Wally Hennessey said nothing Moni Maker does
surprises him.
</P>
<P>
   Magician was parked through the first three quarters of the Nat
Ray and was never a factor, finishing sixth. Nikki Cole Cole was
second and Raffaello Ambrosio third.
</P>
<P>
   Moni Maker took command at the top of the stretch and was never
seriously challenged. She paid $3.30 to win and increased her
career earnings to $5,168,631 -- more than any other harness horse.
</P>
</TEXT>
