and Javier Cardona hit his first major league home run as the
Tigers beat the Minnesota Twins 4-3 Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Juan Encarnacion hit a tiebreaking single for the Tigers in the
sixth that chased Joe Mays (6-13) after Bobby Higginson singled and
Hal Morris drew a two-out walk.
</P>
<P>
