<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockers' McConnell Serio To Retire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- Suzie McConnell Serio, the Cleveland Rockers'
starting point guard since 1998, is retiring at the end of the
season.
</P>
<P>
   A news release issued on Saturday said McConnell Serio and the
team would not comment until a press conference is held Sunday at
5:15 p.m. EDT, before the team's final regular-season home game
against the Washington Mystics.
</P>
<P>
   McConnell Serio has started all 29 games this year, averaging
5.1 points. She is eighth in the WNBA in assists, averaging 3.8.
</P>
<P>
   The 5-foot-5 guard helped the U.S. basketball team win a gold
medal in the 1988 Olympics and the bronze in '92. McConnell Serio,
married with four kids, was coaching girls high school basketball
when she decided to play professionally again in 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland's season-finale is Wednesday at Washington. The
Rockers, in second place in the Eastern Conference, have already
clinched a playoff berth.
</P>
</TEXT>
