<HEADLINE> Clinton Jokes At Kennedy Compound  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HYANNIS PORT, Mass. (AP) -- President Clinton, making his first
visit to the fabled Kennedy family compound, raised eyebrows about
a supposed flirtation with one clan member even as he was raising
campaign cash for another.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton joked that he really wasn't there to raise money for
Maryland Lt. Gov. Kathleen Kennedy Townsend's gubernatorial
campaign, but to see her mother, family matriarch Ethel Kennedy.
</P>
<P>
   The president startled the crowd when he said he would like to
stay overnight at Ethel's house -- and have the newspapers write
about it.
</P>
<P>
   ''Ethel, you may have to put me up tonight -- and if so that
would tickle me, because Ethel's been sending me these raunchy
Valentine cards for years -- and I'm completely in love with her,''
the president said as the audience giggled.
</P>
<P>
   ''And I keep trying to get some tabloid to write something
sleazy about it, and I haven't been able to so far,'' Clinton said.
</P>
<P>
   But Clinton did not linger when his speech was over.
</P>
<P>
   He flew directly back to the island of Martha's Vineyard off the
Massachusetts coast, his headquarters for a weekend fund-raising
whirlwind.
</P>
<P>
   His schedule included two fund-raisers on Martha's Vineyard on
Sunday for his wife, first lady Hillary Rodham Clinton, who is
running for a U.S. Senate seat from New York.
</P>
</TEXT>
