<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sting 84, Starzz 82  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Angie Braziel scored with 2.8 seconds
left as the Charlotte Sting edged Utah 84-82 on Saturday night,
eliminating the Starzz from WNBA playoff contention.
</P>
<P>
   Andrea Stinson led Charlotte with 23 points, while Tracy Reid
scored a season-high 21 points on 10-for-11 shooting as the Sting
(8-22) snapped a four-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer Azzi missed an off-balance 3-pointer at the buzzer for
the Starzz (16-14). The loss secured the final Western Conference
playoff spot for Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   Utah rallied from a nine-point second-half deficit to take a
78-76 lead on Korie Hlede's 3-pointer with 2:22 remaining.
Charlotte bounced back with 3-pointers from Dawn Staley and
Charlotte Smith to go ahead 82-78.
</P>
<P>
   The Starzz cut the lead to two on Adrienne Goodson's layup with
15 seconds remaining. Staley, who had a game-high 10 assists,
turned the ball over on the Sting's next possession, and another
Goodson layup tied the score with nine seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Natalie Williams led Utah with 23 points, including 17 in the
second half, and nine rebounds. Goodson added 22 points and nine
rebounds for the Starzz. Reserve Amy Herrig scored a career-high 14
points, and Hlede added 14 as well.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte shot 57.4 percent from the field, its second highest
percentage of the season.
</P>
<P>
   The first half featured nine ties and 12 lead changes before
Charlotte took a 39-37 lead into the break. Sting center Rhonda
Mapp hyperextended her left knee in the first half and did not
return.
</P>
</TEXT>
